# dig_relight.tas — Skylight recompute-on-dig regression.
#
# Purpose: Verify that removing a block re-floods skylight into the new
# air cell so the newly-exposed floor block reads a correct per-vertex
# skylight value. Before the fix (phase-1 baseline with "no relight on
# dig"), digging even a single block left the exposed floor rendering at
# sky_brightness = 0.05 because `chunk.skylight[x][y][z]` was still 0 from
# when the cell was solid. The fix is to recompute skylight + mark the
# chunk mesh_dirty inside `World.setBlock`.
#
# The script digs four blocks in a small pit (two surface blocks plus two
# blocks one layer down, owing to camera pitch being clamped at
# −π/2 + 0.01 rad which gives the raycast a slight horizontal drift as it
# goes down). Before the fix, those dug blocks render with their newly
# exposed floor/walls at sky_brightness = 0.05 (nearly black). After the
# fix, the new air cells get their skylight recomputed and the pit
# interior shows a natural brightness gradient from rim to floor.
#
# Usage (from utils/swindowzig):
#   zig build native -Dexample=voxel
#   ./zig-out/bin/voxel --world=flatland --aa=none \
#     --tas examples/voxel/tests/dig_relight.tas \
#     --dump-frame=/tmp/dig_relight.ppm
#
#   # Comparison baseline — with --lighting=none, every face is at sky = 1.0
#   # regardless of depth, so the shaft walls are uniformly bright:
#   ./zig-out/bin/voxel --world=flatland --lighting=none --aa=none \
#     --tas examples/voxel/tests/dig_relight.tas \
#     --dump-frame=/tmp/dig_relight_none.ppm
#
# Tick numbering is relative to the first post-loading tick.

# --- Capture mouse ---
1 mouse_down left
2 mouse_up left

# --- Look almost straight down so each subsequent dig chews into the
#     same (x,z) column — we want a 1×N×1 vertical shaft, not a staircase.
#     ao_corners.tas uses 180 and gets a staircase; we need steeper. ---
3 mouse_move 0 400

# --- Dig four blocks deep (1×4×1 vertical shaft).
#     One tick between each dig so the press edge fires cleanly; an extra
#     tick of settle after each dig lets mesh_dirty trigger a full regen
#     before the next click rechecks the raycast. ---
5  mouse_down left
6  mouse_up left
9  mouse_down left
10 mouse_up left
13 mouse_down left
14 mouse_up left
17 mouse_down left
18 mouse_up left

# --- Tilt up so the rim of the hole is in frame too. ---
22 mouse_move 0 -45

# --- Pan slightly so the diagonal interior is exposed, revealing the
#     per-depth brightness gradient on the wall faces. ---
24 mouse_move 5 0
25 mouse_move 5 0
26 mouse_move 5 0
27 mouse_move 5 0
28 mouse_move 5 0

# --- Hold steady so --dump-frame lands on a stable view. ---
34 mouse_move 0 0
